 "coaching": {
  "headline": "Two enemy healers, zero anti-heal — and you lost the objective war 1 to 5, sieged for 70k. The build sheet said anti-heal was mandatory; nobody bought it.",
  "team": "Enemy ran Serath plus a second healer; the comp screen flags anti-heal as non-optional and three of you got the warning. Not one anti-heal item was bought. Predictably you couldn't close fights and they took the map — five objectives to one, 70.4k objective damage to your 10.7k. Cuban's Shinbi was the only favored lane; everything else was behind. Boris jungle (Mr_Meat, a carry-assigned player) and Argus mid (Xeebs, a jungle main) are both off-role again. The pattern from your losses is consistent: off-role lineup + no anti-heal + lost objectives.",
  "whatShiftedIt": "One anti-heal item between the three flagged players turns 'can't close' into 'can close.' That alone shifts the objective math you lost 1-5. Then put Xeebs back in the jungle instead of mid.",
  "perPlayer": {
